# CBC: Chemical Warfare

CBC:CW adds a bunch of new chemicals to be used on the CBC fluid shell, all with custom effects to be very effective against players with or without armor. All chemicals have recipes so they can all be used in survival.

### War Chemicals

*   **Carbon Monoxide** - The easiest of the poisons to obtain, it's not very strong but can be very harmful if ignored, slowly drains your health and blinds you;

*   **Chlorine Gas** - Stronger than vanilla poison, drains health fast and gives you nausea, can be very fatal if not taken care;

*   **Hydrogen Cyanide** - Extremly powerful poison that drains 1/4 of the player health every hit, damage slows as you get lower in hp and cannot kill you, but can leave you at low health very quickly;

*   **Chloroform** - It cannot damage you or even kill you, instead it limits your movement a lot, gives you mining fatigue and weakness plus occasionally give you a short darkness effect;

*   **Ammonium Acetate** - Dosen't damage you either but gives you nausea and hunger for as long as the effect lasts, it's very dangerous if you need to heal quickly because you're always low on hunger;

*   **Napalm** - A very flammable liquid that soaks the player in a never ending fire, at least until it runs out;

*   **Ammonium Nitrate Fuel** - Very useful if used alongside Napalm, soaks the player in a combustible fuel that explodes in contact with fire;

*   **Crystal Blue** - In opposition to other chemicals this one has a good and a bad side, while you're under the Crystal Blue High effect you recieve buffs, but as soon as it runs out, you're left addicted to it losing the buffs and getting slowness and weakness instead unless you become high again;

*   **Mustard Gas** - Does slower damage than other poisons but does double the damage each hit being very dangerous by draining tons of health in a split;

*   **Sulfuric Acid** - Soaks the player with a very potent acid that burns your skin very quickly doing a ton of damage;

*   **Methane** - Slower damage output compared to other chemical poisons, but can be ignited inside of the player if they are set ablaze, doing a ton of extra damage while they are on fire;

*   **Nitroglycerin** - When soaked in it much won't happen, some ocasional random blindness, the real effect happens when the player soaked in it tries to run, bursting into a strong explosion;

*   **Paracetic Acid** - Isn't generally very effective on land, it's a very long lasting weak poison, the real effects happen underwater, where it drains the player oxygen extremly quickly and blinds him;

*   **Phosgene** - It's a mixture of Carbon Monoxide effects and Chlorine Gas, the damage output isn't great, but it's filled with debuffs that will affect vision a lot;

*   **Oxygen** - One of the few beneficial effects, dosen't harm you in any way, instead, it keeps you from losing oxygen when underwater while the effect is on;

*   **Detergent** - When soaked in detergent, it will prevent and remove all chemicals that soak you, dosen't work with poisons.


